}}, [[Boston]]\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}}\n| Female\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{flag|CZE}}\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n| colspan=\"10\" | A woman who attended a [[Biogen]] employee conference at Boston, where COVID-19 was confirmed.<ref name=boston-biogen>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcboston.com/news/local/3-who-attended-biogen-meeting-in-boston-test-positive-for-coronavirus/2086462/|title=3 Who Attended Biogen Meeting in Boston Test Positive for Coronavirus|website=nbcboston.com}}</ref> \n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''16'''\n| 6 March 2020\n| {{Partial failure|Confirmed}}\n| {{Success|Travel-related}}\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{flag|CZE}}\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n| colspan=\"10\" | A person who either came from Italy or was in contact with of one of the cases who returned from Italy, no details provided.<ref name=\"case13-19-twitter\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''17'''\n| 6 March 2020\n| {{Partial failure|Confirmed}}\n| {{Success|Travel-related}}\n| {{flag|Italy}}, [[Auronzo di Cadore]]\n| [[D\u011b\u010d\u00edn]]\n| [[\u00dast\u00ed nad Labem Region]]\n| {{Partial failure|Masaryk Hospital, [[\u00dast\u00ed nad Labem]]}}\n| Female\n| 12\n| {{flag|CZE}}\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n| colspan=\"10\" | The eldest daughter of the infected man from D\u011b\u010d\u00edn (case #3).<ref name=\"case17-18.idnes\">{{cite web|url=https://www.seznamzpravy.cz/clanek/jednim-z-nakazenych-je-prazsky-lekar-i-pres-potize-ordinoval-91374|title=19 cases of coronavirus in the Czech Republic, age from 1 to 68.|website=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES|language=cs |access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''18'''\n| 6 March 2020\n| {{Partial failure|Confirmed}}\n| {{Success|Travel-related}}\n| {{flag|Italy}}, [[Auronzo di Cadore]]\n| [[D\u011b\u010d\u00edn]]\n| [[\u00dast\u00ed nad Labem Region]]\n| {{Partial failure|Masaryk Hospital, 